currentprojection = perspective(6,3,2);

triple A, B, C, O, P, Q;

A = (0,0,0);
B = (6,0,0);
C = (3,sqrt(27),0);
O = (A + B + C)/3;
P = (0,0,4);
Q = (0,0,-4);

draw(B--C--A--cycle);
draw(A--P--B);
draw(A--Q--B);
draw(O--P,dashed);
draw(O--Q,dashed);
draw(O--(O + (P - O)/2),dashed);

label("$A$", A, SW);
label("$B$", B, SE);
label("$C$", C, N);
label("$O$", O, S);
label("$P$", P, N);
label("$Q$", Q, S);
label("$D$", (O + (P - O)/2), W);
[/asy]

Let $D$ be the midpoint of $\overline{PQ}$. Since $O$ is the circumcenter of $\triangle PAB$ and $\triangle QAB$,  $OD$ is perpendicular to both $\overline{PA}$ and $\overline{QA}$.  Hence, $OD$ is perpendicular to plane $PAQ$.

Since $\triangle PAB$ and $\triangle QAB$ are both equilateral triangles,  $PA = PB = QA = QB$. This makes $P$ and $Q$ equidistant from $A$ and $B$, so line $PQ$ is the perpendicular bisector of $\overline{AB}$. 

Since $\triangle ABC$ is equilateral,  $O$ lies on the perpendicular bisector of $\overline{AB}$.  Therefore, $O$ lies on line $PQ$.

Also, $PD = QD = \frac{1}{2} PQ = \frac{1}{2}d$, where $d$ is the diameter of the sphere.

By the Pythagorean Theorem on right triangle $POD$,
\[d^2 = (OD)^2 + (PD)^2 = (150\sqrt{3})^2 + \left( \frac{d}{2} \right)^2.\]Solving, we find $d = \boxed{200\sqrt{3}}$.
